29/09/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Defence Minister Pandeli Majko met on Tuesday (28 September) with NATO Assistant Secretary General Gunter Altenburg. 
They discussed the progress of defence-related reforms and implementation of the national Membership Action Plan. 
Majko briefed Altenburg on the progress made in restructuring the army and achieving NATO standards. 
Altenburg in turn praised Albania's participation in the international peacekeeping missions in Afghanistan and Bosnia and Herzegovina.
Also Tuesday, Albania signed an agreement with Kosovo aimed at avoiding double taxation and boosting economic co-operation. 
Kosovo has already signed a similar agreement with the United States. 
(ATA, RTV21, KosovaLive - 28/09/04)
